      • test_describe

        public void test_describe()
                   throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                          TokenMgrError,
                          ParseException
        Unit test for simple DESCRIBE query. (The main differences between DESCRIBE and SELECT is that the DESCRIBE query allows only a simple list of variables or IRIs in place of the select expressions and involves an implicit CONSTRUCT. Both DESCRIBE and SELECT allow the same solution modifiers.) 
         DESCRIBE ?s where {?s ?p ?o}
        Note: The DESCRIBE projection and where class of the DESCRIBE query are modeled directly, but this does not capture the semantics of the DESCRIBE query. You MUST run an IASTOptimizer to rewrite the QueryBase in order to capture the semantics of a DESCRIBE query.
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException

      • test_bnode_bracket_syntax_05

        public void test_bnode_bracket_syntax_05()
                                  throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                         TokenMgrError,
                                         ParseException
        Unit test for blank node "[]" syntax. 
         PREFIX foaf: 
 SELECT * {
   [ foaf:name ?name ;
     foaf:mbox 
   ]
 }
        Note that this has exactly the same interpretation as: 
         PREFIX foaf: 
 SELECT * {
   _:b18 foaf:name ?name .
   _:b18 foaf:mbox 
 }
        assuming that the blank node is given the identity _:b18.

        Note: blank nodes are translated into anonymous variables in the parse tree before the bigdata AST model is generated.

        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException
